# CORRELATION - Correlation is the direct relationship between two variables, and the strength of that relationship. Understanding how variables are correlated, can help us predict future outcomes. A quick method to see the correlation of numeric columns is though:

.corr()

# A negative correlation coefficient indicates that as one variable increases, the other decreases. A value closer to zero suggests that there is a weak relationship between the variables, whereas a value closer to one or negative one suggests a relationship. Note: .corr calculates the Pearson correlation coefficient, which measures the linear relationship between two varibables.

